Package: jzip
Version: 2.1
Revision: 1
Description: John's Zcode InterPreter runs Infocom & Inform bytecodegames
Homepage: http://jzip.sourceforge.net/
License: BSD
DescDetail: <<
 John's Zcode InterPreter. Runs Infocom & Inform bytecode images
 (games) like Zork. Unicode/multicodepage support is planned.

 - To play the truly original "dungeon" game, the data file you want is:
   ftp://ftp.gmd.de/if-archive/games/zcode/zdungeon.z5
 - Put zdungeon.z5 into /sw/share/infocom/
 - Open a NEW terminal window then run: jzip zdungeon.z5

 Known problems: Segmentation fault upon quitting, otherwise it works fine.
 http://www.macosxhints.com/article.php?story=20010407020830755
<<
Recommends: infocom-zork
Suggests: frotz, inform, ztools
Source: mirror:sourceforge:%n/%n21-10oct2000.zip
Source-MD5: 4c03c95bec15e45477899c12a545fc1d
Sourcedirectory: .
CompileScript: make -f unixio.mak jzip ckifzs LIBS='-lz -lncurses -L%p/lib' OPTIMIZE='-O3 -g3 -prebind' CFLAGS='$(OPTIMIZE) -DPOSIX -DHARD_COLORS -DUSE_ZLIB'
InstallScript: <<
 mkdir -p %i/bin/
 mkdir -p %i/share/infocom/
 install -m 755 jzip %i/bin/
 install -m 755 ckifzs %i/bin/
 tail -n 22 license.c | head -20 | sed 's@.\{12\}@@' | sed 's@\\n\|"\|);@@g' | sed 's@ZIPVER@Jzip V%v@g' > license.txt
<<
